name: Butterfly Cloud
category: Decorative
footprint: 2x2
facing: no
shadow: no
blocks_light: no
height: 1.5
placement: floor
room_types: forest-clearing, meadow, fey-glade, druid-grove, garden, fey-court
typical_count: single
clusters_with: wildflower-patch, flower-patch, tree, shrub
notes: Cluster of butterflies fluttering in the air above flowers. Seen from above — small winged dots at varying heights creating depth.
---
# footprint 2x2: x 0-2, y 0-2
# Overhead/airborne prop — no shadow, no light-block

# === Faint ground-shadow hint beneath the cloud (subtle) ===
ellipse 1.00,1.00 0.60,0.50 fill #1a0a00 0.06

# === Butterflies at different positions ===
# Each butterfly: two wing ellipses (one per side), tiny body line, small antennae hint

# --- Butterfly 1 — orange monarch at (0.45, 0.45) ---
